<p>I'd like to observe changes to a key path per <a href="http://docs.ractivejs.org/latest/ractive-observe" rel="nofollow">docs on ractive observe</a>. However, I'd like to be able to observe multiple paths at the same time, eg, given:</p>  <pre><code>var binding = new Ractive({   el: '.here',   data: {     items: [       {         finished: false       },       {         finished: false       }       ]   },   template: someTemplate }) </code></pre>  <p>I'd like to be able to do something like:</p>  <pre><code>binding.observe('items.*.finished') </code></pre>  <p>Or similar to be able to watch the <code>finished</code> property of any item in the array.</p>  <p>What's the best way to do this?</p>